        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURES 30–33. 30. Lectotype of Rhyacophila fasciata Hagen 1859 (male). 30a, thorax and right forewing (pinned); 30b, abdomen and male genitalia in cork-stoppered microvial (ethanol), detail. Photos: Museum of Comparative Zoology of Harvard University, Cambridge, MA, USA (MCZH). 31–33. Rhyacophila septentrionis MacLachlan 1865. 31, lectotype (male): 31a, specimen (pinned); 31b, apicodorsal lobe of segment IX and preanal appendages, dorsal view; 31c, detail of genitalia, posterior view. 32, female: 32a, cleared and mounted genitalia; 32b, original mounting preparation. 33, original mounting preparation of R. septentrionis male genitalia. Photos: Ben Price, Natural History Museum of United Kingdom (NHMUK)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4804108/files/figure.png" .

